==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic, corresponding to [[for-]] + [[giefan|ġiefan]].  Cognate with Old Saxon [[fargeban]] (Dutch [[vergeven]]), Old High German [[fargeban]] (German [[vergeben]]), Old Norse [[fyrigefa]], Gothic [[𐍆𐍂𐌰𐌲𐌹𐌱𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/for'jievan/}}

===Verb===
'''forġiefan''' (class V strong: ''3 singular present'' '''[[forgiefþ|forġiefþ]]''', ''3 singular preterite'' '''[[forgeaf|forġeaf]]''', ''preterite plural'' '''[[forgeafon|forġēafon]]''', ''past participle'' '''[[forgiefen|forġiefen]]''')
# to [[give]] up, [[bestow]], [[grant]]
# to [[forgive]] ''(in translation of Latin [[perdonare]])''

===Descendants===
*English [[forgive]]

